# Next.js App Router Conventions

## Route Structure

```
src/app/
  auth/            ‚Üí /auth/*         (login, MFA, forgot-password)
  mgt/             ‚Üí /mgt/*          (management portal)
    (wfm)/         ‚Üí route group     (rosters, studio-tracker, configuration)
    (hr)/          ‚Üí route group     (employees, leaves, swaps, attendance, organizations)
    (training)/    ‚Üí route group     (training)
  gp/              ‚Üí /gp/*           (GP employee portal)
  offline/         ‚Üí /offline        (PWA offline fallback)
```

- Parenthesized folders are route groups ‚Äî do NOT create URL segments
- Feature components live co-located in `components/` subdirectories next to their page
- Do NOT create new top-level route directories ‚Äî features go inside `(wfm)`, `(hr)`, etc.

## Client vs Server Boundaries

- This project is client-heavy: 100+ `'use client'` files, zero `'use server'` directives
- Root `layout.tsx` is the only meaningful server component (fetches locale/messages)
- Default to `'use client'` for new pages unless the page has zero interactivity

**Critical SSR safety rule**: Any code accessing `window`, `document`, `navigator`, `localStorage`, or `sessionStorage` MUST guard with:

```typescript
if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
  // browser-only code
}
```

Or use `storageManager` from `@/utils/storageManager` which handles this internally.

## Error Handling Gap

No `error.tsx` files exist in the codebase. When adding critical features, create `error.tsx` alongside the page:

```typescript
'use client';
export default function Error({ error, reset }: { error: Error; reset: () => void }) {
  return <ErrorFallback error={error} onRetry={reset} />;
}
```

No `loading.tsx` files exist either. Loading states are handled via RTK Query's `isLoading` flags and Mantine skeletons.

## Middleware (`src/middleware.ts`)

- Matcher: `['/', '/auth/:path*', '/gp/:path*', '/mgt/:path*']`
- Decodes JWT from `ID_TOKEN` cookie, extracts `custom:role`
- Enforces: GP users to `/gp/*`, MGT users to `/mgt/*`
- Environment gates: studio-tracker and organizations are dev-only
- Unauthenticated users redirect to `/auth/login`
- **New protected routes MUST be added to the matcher pattern**

## Layouts

| Layout | Location | Provides |
|---|---|---|
| Root | `src/app/layout.tsx` | NextIntl, Redux, Mantine, Modals, Analytics, PWA |
| MGT | `src/app/mgt/layout.tsx` | Sidebar navigation (`mgt-layout`) |
| GP | `src/app/gp/layout.tsx` | Bottom navigation bar (`gp-layout`) |
| Auth | `src/app/auth/login/layout.tsx` | Suspense wrapper |

## Route Constants

Import from `@/routes` ‚Äî never hardcode paths:

```typescript
import { Routes } from '@/routes';
// Routes.MGT.WFM.ROSTERS.ROSTER_CURRENT  ‚Äî NOT '/mgt/roster-current'
// Routes.GP.SCHEDULE                       ‚Äî NOT '/gp/schedule'
```

## Config Gotchas

- `trailingSlash: true` ‚Äî all routes end with `/`, affects redirects and links
- `output: 'standalone'` ‚Äî Docker deployment, no `node_modules` in container
- `reactStrictMode: false` ‚Äî effects only fire once (no double-invoke in dev)
- `compress: true` ‚Äî gzip enabled at Next.js level
